INSERT INTO `armi` VALUES (1,'Fire Knight\'s Shortsword','Shortsword used by the Fire Knights. A slender blade that undulates like fire. Blessed with a flame incantation. Further flame imbuement will amplify the effect and greatly increase the armament\'s power.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/fire_knights_shortsword_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'- Has a 4.0% chance to drop by Fire Knights wielding this weapon in Shadow Keep.\r\n- Can be farmed by dropping down and killing the Fire Knight below the Storehouse, Loft site of Grace and the Fire Knight just east of the Storehouse, Seventh Floor site of grace.'),(2,'Main-gauche','Dagger with a large hand guard.\r\n\r\nIntended to be used in the left hand, thereby complementing a piercing sword or identical blade held in the right to enable a distinctive style of fighting.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/main-gauche_dagger_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'Shadow Keep: From the Main Gate Plaza site of grace go west and up the stairs until the soldier ambushes you, then enter that room and on the right there is another doorway. The item is in there protected by two soldiers and a blacksteel knight.'),(3,'Dagger','A standard dagger with a straight blade.\r\n\r\nThough modest in reach and capacity for harm, this weapon is light enough to jab in rapid succession and delivers devastating critical hits. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/dagger_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',1.5,'- Can be purchased from Twin Maiden Husks at the Roundtable Hold for 400 Runes.\r\n- Can be dropped by Highwaymen and different types of Foot Soldiers.\r\nMultiple soldiers can be encountered early in the game at the camp east of Warmaster\'s Shack.\r\n- Has a 4.00% chance to drop from Messmer Foot Soldier'),(4,'Parrying Dagger','A knife with curved handguards. Designed to parry, turning foes\' attacks against them. \r\n\r\nFor master of combat who anticipate every enemy strike and counter accordingly, this weapon is all they need.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/parrying_dagger_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',1.5,'Sold by Patches at Murkwater Cave for 1600 Runes after he sets up shop.\r\nCan be purchased from Twin Maiden Husks at the Roundtable Hold after giving them Patches\' Bell Bearing.'),(5,'Miséricorde','Dagger favored by military physicians in white. \r\nThe pointed blade is hard and sharp, making critical hits especially potent. \r\n\r\nMedicine is mercy. and mercy upon the battlefield is ruthless. Beware the killers clothed as men of compassion.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/misericorde_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'- Location: Stormveil Castle.\r\n- Can be looted off a corpse that can be found in the large armory room, next to the fortress of the Grafted Scion.\r\n- You will need to use the Stonesword Key on the imp statue to dispel the white fog that\'s blocking the doorway.'),(6,'Great Knife','Large knife with a broad, curved blade.\r\n\r\nThis weapon is designed to slash and rend, inflicting blood loss upon the recipient. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/great_knife_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',1.5,'- Starting equipment for the Bandit class.\r\n- Rare drop from Demi-Humans wielding this weapon.\r\n- Craftman\'s Shack: four Demi-Humans hiding in a flock of sheep north of the Site of Grace.\r\n- Lakeside Crystal Cave: one Demi-Human hiding in a bush at the start of the dungeon.\r\n- Volcano Cave: Can be farmed from two Demi-Humans just outside of the cave '),(7,'Bloodstained Dagger','Dagger with a bloodstained blade.\r\nAfflicts targets with blood loss.\r\n\r\nAs blood darkened the dagger through repeated slashing and stabbing, its blade only grew sharper and harder.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/bloodstained_dagger_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'- Rare drop from Demi-Human Chiefs\r\n- There is a Demi-Human Chief sleeping before the wooden bridge leading to the Minor Erdtree in the weeping peninsula.\r\n- There are 2 of them close to each other in the Hermit Village. A quick way to farm is going to Primeval Sorcerer Azur grace, hugging the wall while going south and there will be one of them isolated. Kill that one and there is one immediately to the side away from the wall.\r\n- Shadow of the Erdtree - Cerulean Coast: One can be found in a cave near this Scadutree Fragment. The other one can be found protecting this Field Boss.'),(8,'Erdsteel Dagger','An erdsteel dagger with a grass crest engraved upon its blade. Carried by the Erdtree royalty for self-defense in times of peace. \r\n\r\nThough forged to a high standard, the weapon is difficult to wield. \r\nAttack power also scales with faith. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/erdsteel_dagger_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'- Given by Kenneth Haight as a reward for clearing out Fort Haight.\r\n- Found NW of the Avenue Balcony site of Leyndell, Royal Capital. Drop down a pit with a Broken Statue and it will be on a corpse.'),(9,'Wakizashi','Short sword with a tempering pattern on the blade. A weapon unique to warriors of the Land of Reeds. Afflicts targets with blood loss.\r\n\r\nThese swords are considered auxiliary weapons. Yet, one man is known to wield this weapon in his left hand while using a full-sized katana in his right. A demonic swordsman known only as Okina.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/wakizashi_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',3.0,'- Inside Gaol Cave, found inside one of the locked cells. The player must unlock the cells first.'),(10,'Celebrant\'s Sickle','Sickle decorated with flowers and many-coloured fabrics. Ceremonial tool used by dancers during the festivities of Dominula. Its attacks can slip through an enemy\'s guard.\r\n\r\nCrafted from human bone.\r\n\r\nGrants trace amounts of runes on landing attacks.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/celebrants-sickle_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',1.5,'- Rare drop from the Celebrants wielding it at the Windmill Village.\r\n- These enemies are easily recognizable by their blue coats. Two are found in the large group midway between the Windmill Village and Windmill Heights Sites of Grace. These enemies are passive until provoked, and in addition to the weapon have a chance to drop Human Bone Shards and Golden Runes [3], so farming them can be both easy and lucrative. This group also contains two Celebrants who can drop Celebrant\'s Rib-Rake.'),(11,'Ivory Sickle','Sickle fashioned from ivory. \r\nWeapon carried by aged Albunaurics.\r\n\r\nThese weapons are evidence of their dedication to the Haligtree, despite never having entered its presence. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/ivory_sickle_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'Can be found at the Village of the Albinaurics. It is up a small hill past the grace in a stone coffin.'),(12,'Crystal Knife','A knife made by sharpening hard crystal.\r\nSignature weapon of glintstone miners. \r\n\r\nUsed as a tool to extract glintstone from broken rock, and as such a faint magic enwreathes the blade.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/crystal_knife_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'Found in a chest inside the Raya Lucaria Crystal Tunnel, in a storage area three levels down, guarded by Marionettes.'),(13,'Scorpion\'s Stinger','Dagger fashioned from a great scorpion\'s tail, glistening with scarlet rot.\r\n\r\nA ceremonial tool used by heretics, crafted from the relic of a sealed outer god.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/scorpions_stinger_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.5,'Found in the Lake of Rot. Cross the swamp and go through the entrance with large statues on either side to reach the Grand Cloister Site of Grace. Use the ledges to drop down to the bottom, and head straight ahead (westward) and you\'ll find the dagger in a chest.'),(14,'Cinquedea','Short sword given to high ranking clergymen of Farum Azula.\r\nRaises potency of bestial incantations.\r\n\r\nThe design celebrates a beast\'s five fingers, symbolic of the intelligence once granted upon their kind.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/cinquedea_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',3.5,'- Location: Cinquedea can be found at the bottom of the exterior structure of the Bestial Sanctum, near a broken rat corpse statue.\r\n- To reach this spot, go to the west cliff outside the sanctum and travel down a series of roots and platforms. Jump down to the outlying branch and continue downward using the ledges and pillars. You can use Rainbow Stones to figure out where to fall from next.'),(15,'Glintstone Kris','Ritual blade once presented to Leyndell by the Academy of Raya Lucaria to celebrate their newfound peace.\r\n\r\nThough the weapon is embedded with precious glintstones and features Erdtree ornamentation, the undulating blade is symbolic of an ancient ritual.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/glintstone_kris_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',1.5,'Rewarded to players for progressing through the Sorceress Sellen questline and siding with her.'),(16,'Reduvia','Jagged dagger with a distinctive curled blade.\r\nCarried by the noble servants of the Lord of Blood.\r\n\r\nThis dagger rips the flesh as it enters, inflicting blood loss with sickening efficacy. A proud testament to the success of its vicious design, this weapon is perpetually coated in blood.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/reduvia_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.5,'Dropped by Bloody Finger Nerijus.'),(17,'Blade of Calling','Dagger given to one who set out on a journey to fulfill her duty long ago.\r\nThe power of its former owner, the kindling maiden, is still apparent.\r\n\r\nThe one who walks alongside flame,\r\nShall one day meet the road of Destined Death.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/blade_of_calling_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',1.5,'From the Forbidden Lands site of grace, turn back and head towards the elevator. Face west-southwest, then activate the elevator and watch for an opening to jump off into. The Blade of Calling is on the table in the room at the end of this hall.'),(18,'Black Knife','Dagger once belonging to one of the assassins who murdered Godwyn the Golden on the Night of the Black Knives. \r\n\r\nA ritual performed on the oddly misshapen blade imbued it with the power of the stolen Rune of Death. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/black_knife_dagger_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','DAG',2.0,'This is a drop from defeating the Black Knife Assassin at the entrance of Sainted Hero\'s Grave, in Altus Plateau. This boss is directly west of the Rampartside Path site.'),(19,'Velvet Sword of St. Trina','Silver sword of St. Trina, now stained the color of velvet. Inflicts eternal sleep. When St. Trina was abandoned, the faint, light-purple mists coalesced into an intoxicating deep-purple cloud.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/velvet_sword_of_st_trina_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',2.5,'Stone Coffin Fissure: From the Fissure Cross site of grace, walk immediately north-west to the closest giant coffin that\'s tilted nearly vertical. Climb down to a ledge that passes underneath the brick platform nearest the site of grace. The sword is in a small cave network there and guarded by several putrescent oozes.'),(20,'Stone-Sheathed Sword','A sword that none can pull from its scabbard of cracked stone. Relic of a lost civilization from a time long past, said to have served a ritual purpose at altars of light and darkness.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/stone-sheathed_sword_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',5.0,'- Can be acquired at one of the 3 Altar locations:\r\n- Fog Rift Catacombs (on top of the 3 trap platforms and run to the furthest right corner)\r\n- Ruins of Unte (behind the inactive Furnace Golem, to the right from the chest that holds Giant Golden Arc)\r\n- Ancient Ruins of Rauh (on a tower connected by an invisible bridge beyond a large room of Kindred of Rot).\r\n- The first of the three altars you interact with will grant you the Stone-Sheathed Sword. Once the sword is obtained, interacting with the other two altars will transform it into either Sword of Darkness or Sword of Light.\r\n- After first transforming it to the Sword of Darkness or Light, interacting with the other altar will transform it to the other. This can be repeated indefinitely. The Sword\'s upgrade levels are retained when you transform it; i.e. transforming a Stone-Sheathed Sword +9 will get you a Sword of Light/Darkness +9.\r\n- The altar with the highest elevation (Rauh > Unte > Catacombs) will transform the sword into the Sword of Light. The altar with the lower elevation will transform it into the Sword of Darkness.\r\n- The Stone-Sheathed Sword will be permanently lost if it is converted into the Sword of Darkness or Sword of Light. The only way to acquire another example of the weapon is via NG+.'),(21,'Sword of Light','Sword of light, pulled from its stone scabbard at an altar. From the quick of the root, unswerving rays of light intersect and reflect to give the silver blade form.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/sword_of_light_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',4.0,'- Obtained by acquiring the Stone-Sheathed Sword or Sword of Darkness (see below):\r\n- You can get Stone-Sheathed Sword at one of the 3 Altar locations: Fog Rift Catacombs (on top of the 3 trap platforms and run to the furthest right corner), Ruins of Unte (flowery courtyard), or Ancient Ruins of Rauh (on a tower connected by invisible floor). Once acquired, the altar from which the sword is acquired will become inert, and the sword can then be transformed into the Sword of Darkness or Sword of Light at one of the 2 other Altars.\r\n- It is recommended to acquire the Stone-Sheathed Sword from the Fog Rift Catacombs, as the labyrinthine nature of the dungeon makes it ill-suited for repeated visits should players wish to change the Sword to either its light or dark variants.'),(22,'Sword of Darkness','Sword of darkness, pulled from its stone scabbard at an altar. From the quick of the root, wandering coils of darkness coalesce and release, their eddies and vortices giving form to the dark blade.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/sword_of_darkness_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',4.0,'- Obtained by raising Stone-Sheathed Sword or Sword of Light (see below):\r\n- You can get Stone-Sheathed Sword at one of the 3 Altar locations: Fog Rift Catacombs (on top of the 3 trap platforms and run to the furthest right corner), Ruins of Unte (flowery courtyard), or Ancient Ruins of Rauh (on a tower connected by invisible floor). Once acquired, the altar from which the sword is acquired will become inert, and the sword can then be transformed into the Sword of Darkness or Sword of Light at one of the 2 other Altars.\r\n- It is recommended to acquire the Stone-Sheathed Sword from the Fog Rift Catacombs, as the labyrinthine nature of the dungeon makes it ill-suited for repeated visits should players wish to change the Sword to either its light or dark variants.'),(23,'Short Sword','A short straight sword with a short blade. \r\nIn addition to its reliable standard damage, this weapon also boasts powerful piercing attacks. \r\n\r\nLightweight amongst straight swords, this weapon is easy to wield, requiring only humble attributes. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/short_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.0,'- Starting Equipment for the Astrologer Class.\r\n- Can be purchased from the Nomadic Merchant in North Limgrave for 600 Runes.\r\n- Dropped by Highwaymen in Murkwater Cave.\r\n- Has a 4.00% chance to drop from Messmer Foot Soldier'),(24,'Longsword','A straight sword with a double-edged blade.\r\nIn addition to its easily-inflicted standard damage, this well-balanced weapon can also perform powerful piercing attacks.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/longsword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.5,'Starting equipment for the Vagabond class.\r\nCan be purchased from Twin Maiden Husks at the Roundtable Hold for 1,000 Runes.'),(25,'Broadsword','A straight sword with a wide blade, suited to slashing attacks.\r\n\r\nHorizontal swings boast wide attack range, making it easier to connect with foes. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/broadsword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',4.0,'Starting Equipment for the Confessor Class\r\nCan be bought from the Nomadic Merchant for 1800 Runes. He is located south-east of Coastal Cave.'),(26,'Weathered Straight Sword','Straight sword with a rather short but wide blade.\r\n\r\nSimple to wield, it was known as the sword of the people.\r\nThough the Erdtree styling is still visible, time has not been kind\r\nto this sword, now merely a shadow of its former self.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/weathered_straight_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.0,'Dropped from Commoner enemies in any area.\r\nCan be farmed very early on in the Ailing Village in the Weeping Peninsula.\r\nNear the Secluded Cell grace in Stormveil castle, there is a room full of 10 commoners above the Living Jars that all carry the weapon. Run West from the Secluded Cell site of grace and up the ramp towards the Living Jars. Turn around and hug the wall on the left across the wooden balcony until you reach the end. Jump across to the golden ledge and follow that through a window on the opposite wall. Follow this path around and up until you find a storage room with the 10 sleeping commoners.\r\nA convenient farming spot to get both the armor set and weapon. Takes around 20-30 seconds to navigate to the room although you won\'t have to worry about enemies on the way. The room can be cleared quickly (~15-20 seconds if you can one-shot them) as they are all near each other. Teleport back to the Secluded Cell grace and repeat.'),(27,'Lordsworn\'s Straight Sword','Well-crafted straight sword with an illustrious design, wielded by regulars of a lord\'s army.\r\n\r\nThough blackened and damaged by years of use, it appears to have otherwise been kept in a servicable condition, despite the soldiers having long since lost their minds.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/lordsworns_straight_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.5,'May be dropped by Godrick Soldier in Gatefront Ruins.\r\nCan be dropped by the headless, undead Soldier at Fourth Church of Marika.\r\nThe earliest and easiest grinding spot for this is the Gatefront Ruins, not just for this sword, but all of the weapons that the soldiers use excluding their spear.'),(28,'Noble\'s Slender Sword','Narrow blade carried by wandering nobles.\r\nMade to be easy to wield.\r\n\r\nDaubed with gold from tip to tail, it should fetch a good sum.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/nobles_slender_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.5,'Dropped by Wandering Nobles around Limgrave.\r\nCan be farmed from the group of Wandering Nobles among the Troll-pulled Carriage\'s caravan to the west of Waypoint Ruins, north of Agheel Lake South Site of Grace.\r\nDropped by Wandering Nobles in Raya Lucaria Academy.\r\nCan be farmed from the large group of nobles that appear to the north of the Debate Parlor Site of Grace in Raya Lucaria Academy. Leave the boss room and go up the stairs into a large courtyard. To the left there are two nobles picking weeds, and many more up the stairs near them, in front of two Glintstone Sorcerers. Each Wandering Noble has a chance to drop the sword.\r\nDropped by Wandering Nobles in Caelid, in the graveyard directly south of the Caelid Highway South Site of Grace.\r\nGo to the Church of Pilgrimage site of grace and move down the road leading to the church. There\'s a noble with this sword among the other nobles that can be farmed.\r\nDropped by nobles just east across the bridge from the Bridge of Iniquity site of grace.'),(29,'Cane Sword','Beloved sword of an aged knight whose last quest was long behind\r\nhim, repurposed into a walking stick. The tip is rather worn.\r\n\r\nThough bent of back and without the brawn required even to\r\nraise the sword aloft, still he wished to meet his end with weapon\r\nin hand.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/cane_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',2.5,'Leyndell, Royal Capital, West Capital Rampart Site of Grace: Go south out of the room with the site of grace and down the flight of stairs to the floor underneath, make a complete U-turn in the room with the stairs to find a corpse with the sword.\r\nThe item can still be acquired in Leyndell, Ashen Capital. From the Leyndell, Capital of Ash Site of Grace, head west towards the dragon corpse\'s wing. Behind the wing, climb inside the broken wall, climb the ladder and keep going until you meet the same flight of stairs. Make a U-turn in the room down the stairs and the sword can be looted from the corpse at the end of the room.'),(30,'Warhawk\'s Talon','Talon-swords are affixed to the legs of the Stormveil\'s warhawks, but this one has been repurposed for human use.\r\n\r\nThe blade is thin and lightweight so as not to obstruct the hawk\'s mobility.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/warhawks_talon_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.0,'Can be found in Stormveil Castle as drop by defeating Warhawks. There are four immediately out the door from the Rampart Tower site of grace.'),(31,'Lazuli Glintstone Sword','A sword with a glintstone in its handguards. Wielded by scholars of the Lazuli Conspectus who seek to master Carian sorcery. Deals magic damage.\r\n\r\nApparently once used as a staff of sorcery, this sword is made of wood.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/lazuli_glintstone_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.5,'Chance to drop from the Lazuli Sorcerers found in most areas of Raya Lucaria Academy or Caria Manor.\r\nA good place to farm is directly south of the Schoolhouse Classroom Site of Grace. He is very close to the grace.'),(32,'Carian Knight\'s Sword','Straight sword embedded with a blue glintstone. \r\nWeapon of knights sworn to Carian royalty.\r\n\r\nThese knights\' swords could serve as catalysts, letting them wield sorcerous battle skills. Despite numbering fewer than twenty, this power made them a match for even the champions of gold in battle.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/carian_knights_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',4.0,'Found in a chest in the back of a Carriage being pulled by two Trolls. Go to the Foot of the Four Belfries site of grace and ride north to encounter the Trolls.'),(33,'Crystal Sword','Sword fashioned from pure crystal; a deed impossible for a human. Enwreathed with powerful magic, its attack scales with intelligence. The inscrutable Crystalians have but one clear purpose; to safeguard their crystals unto the end. One theory posits that they yearn for the return of their creator who will carve for them new brethren. ','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/crystal_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',4.5,'Can be found at Village of the Albinaurics. Past the well and across the wooden bridge, on a body near the edge.'),(34,'Rotten Crystal Sword','Sword fashioned from pure crystal; a deed impossible for a human.\r\nIt festers with scarlet rot.\r\n\r\nEnwreathed with powerful magic, its attack scales with intelligence.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/rotten_crystal_sword_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',4.5,'Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree: Found in a chest by the inner wall guarded by 3 Lesser Crystallians. From the Elphael Inner Wall site of grace, head down the steps and jump up on the rubble to your left. You can engage the Lesser Crystallians one by one by luring them over the rubble and into the hallway.'),(35,'Miquellan Knight\'s Sword','Sword forged by servants of Miquella of the Haligtree, with a design modeled after those carried by Carian knights. Instead of glintstone however, amber from the Haligtree is embedded in the blade.\r\nA sumptuous piece, yet it has never been offered to any knight — an ill-starred sword with no master. Skill: Sacred Blade','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/miquellan_knights_sword_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.5,'Elphael, Brace of the Haligtree: Found atop a bell tower. From the Prayer Room site of grace, walk forward into the Haligtree. Not far from the Prayer Room, you will see a Haligtree Soldier sitting down. Before the soldier is a ledge to the right you can walk out on, attached to a tower. Walk on this connector all the way to the tower. Drop down on the tower\'s ledge, and walk this outer rim to the opposite side. There will be a ladder that takes you up to the sword.\r\nAlternatively, if you\'ve already unlocked the Haligtree Roots site of grace, simply take the elevator in the adjacent room with the Scarlet Aeonia bloom (not the one in Malenia\'s boss room). After the elevator stops, get out, walk around the tower and find the ladder. It will take you up to the sword.'),(36,'Ornamental Straight Sword','Slender straight sword patterned after an antique ornament.\r\nSuperior swordsmen prefer to wield one in each hand.\r\n\r\nAfter falling from grace, the dregs of the golden lineage sought power and purpose in the past.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/ornamental_straight_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.0,'Dropped by the Grafted Scion at the Chapel of Anticipation. Players can return to this area after tutorial by using the waygate at The Four Belfries. '),(37,'Golden Epitaph','A sword made to commemorate the death of Godwyn the Golden, first of the demigods to die.\r\n\r\nInfused with the humble prayer of a young boy; \"O brother, lord brother, please die a true death.\"','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/golden_epitaph_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.5,'Auriza Hero\'s Grave: Found on a corpse in a room locked behind an Imp Statue Seal just past the Site of Grace near the entrance. Use a Stonesword Key to unlock the seal and beware the Basilisk guarding the treasure.'),(38,'Sword of St Trina','Silver sword carried by clerics of St. Trina. Inflicts sleep ailment upon foes.\r\nSt. Trina is an enigmatic figure. Some say she is a comely young girl, others are sure he is a boy. The only certainty is that their appearance was as sudden as their disappearance.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/sword_of_st_trina_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',3.0,'In the Forsaken Ruins, near the Rotview Balcony Site of Grace, behind an Imp Seal requiring one Stonesword Key.\r\nThis weapon is very easy to get at a very low-level as a sorcerer. With just 18 int, rock sling, and ideally the meteorite staff, you can stand on the balcony near the site of grace and attack the crows. The first hit will knock them to the ground, and then you can just fling rocks at them until they die and they will be completely unable to attack you since they can\'t reach you. Once you\'ve killed the two that matter, you can go down the cliff on the left and get to the area very easily and safely.'),(39,'Regalia of Eochaid','Treasured sword of Eochaid, a lesser, long-vanished domain. The copper coloration is not to be confused for rust, but is a conduit for its wielder to move it by their will alone. \r\n\r\nSwords of Eochaid dance through the skies','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/regalia_of_eochaid_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',5.5,'Going through the Gaol Cave and reaching the end of the dungeon.\r\nAn alternative route would be to start at the Third Church of Marika and face Southeast. Ride your horse until the cliff meets the water. The cliffside here should have a more red hue to it than the rest of the rock found in Limgrave. If you’re facing the wall due East you’ll notice a cragged vertical line where one part of the cliff face is protruding from another. Double jump on Torrent while following that line and you should now be riding up the cliff face. Now turn your camera to face Northeast, you’ll notice what appears to be an arrowhead of grey stone forming a flat surface among the red-hued cliff. Jump there, then turn the camera South. While it doesn’t look feasible, sprint jump with torrent towards the protrusion across the before mentioned cragged vertical line. When you land, quickly double jump (facing East) to get on top of the ledge. You’ll notice above you several steps in the cliff face just slightly to the right- climb those. Then, jump due North onto the final platform. You will now be above the cliff and able to drop down to the weapon.'),(40,'Coded Sword','Hidden sword once granted to the Tarnished of the Roundtable\r\nby the Two Fingers. A formless cipher comprises its blade, which\r\ndeals holy damage no shield can repel. Champions would gather\r\nat the Roundtable Hold in days long past, when the Two Fingers\r\nwere masters of oration, their flesh yet full of vigor.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/coded_sword_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',2.5,'Found in upstairs throne room of Fortified Manor, Leyndell Royal Capital. From Fortified Manor, 1st Floor site of grace, head outside the building, turn right, climb the stable roofs to the right and re-enter the second floor of the Fortified Manor. Head towards the Round Table room, and the Coded Sword is on the throne of the Throne Room southwest of the Round Table. \r\nThis weapon must be acquired before defeating Maliketh, the Black Blade, as it is not accessible in Leyndell, Ashen Capital.'),(41,'Sword of Night and Flame','Storied sword and treasure of Caria Manor.\r\nOne of the legendary armaments.\r\n\r\nAstrologers, who preceded the sorcerers, established themselves in mountaintops that nearly touched the sky, and considered the Fire Giants their neighbors.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/sword_of_night_and_flame_straight_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD',4.0,'The Sword of Night and Flame weapon can be found in Caria Manor in a locked room behind the gardens in the east side of the manor.\r\n\r\nBegin at the Manor Lower Level site of grace and proceed east across the rooftops, being wary of any spirit soldiers that may appear. From the first intersection, head north and continue down the pathway until the next junction is reached.\r\nAt this next junction, face north and continue for a few steps.\r\nLooking down over the edge of the walkway (around halfway through to the next junction), you should see a platform containing a ladder. This is your goal -- see image below. You can jump from the walkway down onto the upper roof, then down again to reach the platform where the ladder is.\r\nOnce you\'ve descended the ladder, there will be a chest containing the sword next to a chair near the center of the room.'),(42,'Lizard Greatsword','A peculiar weapon carried by imps.\r\nGreatsword smithed in the shape of a fork-tongued lizard.\r\n\r\nStrong attacks allow the wielder to fire the forked tongue from the blade.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/lizard_greatsword_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',9.5,'Dropped by the imps in the Scorpion River Catacombs. \r\nDropped by the imps in the Fog Rift Catacombs (can be farmed from first fought imp).'),(43,'Greatsword of Damnation','Golden greatsword that once pierced the body of Midra, master of the manse. Used by the hornsent in the execution of a damnation like no other.\r\n\r\nThe barbs that pierce the victim from within wind gently around the blade.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/greatsword_of_damnation_greatsword_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',8.0,'Trade Midra, Lord Of Frenzied Flame\'s Remembrance with Enia at Roundtable Hold.'),(44,'Greatsword of Solitude','Steel greatsword wielded by the Knights of the Solitary Gaol. Through a secret rite, they relinquished their hearts for heightened battle prowess. Next, they engraved their blades with two crests: one depicting the light of birth, and the other, solitude.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/greatsword_of_solitude_elden_ring_shadow_of_the_erdtree_dlc_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',15.5,'This item is obtained after defeating the Blackgaol Knight. This boss is located inside the Western Nameless Mausoleum.'),(45,'Bastard Sword','A large sword with a straight blade.\r\nThis heavy sword is normally wielded with two hands, but those with sufficient strength can wield it in one alone.\r\nThe hefty blade can be swung into multiple foes at once thanks to the broad, sweeping attack, making fending off crowds all the easier.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/bastard_sword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',9.0,'Purchased from the Nomadic Merchant at the Castle Morne Rampart Site of Grace, on the eastern side of Weeping Peninsula, for 3.000 Runes.'),(46,'Claymore','A large sword with a long, straight blade. This heavy sword is usually wielded with two hands, but for those with enough strength, one is sufficient.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the heavy sweeping attacks, it can also make a heavy piercing thrust making this a versatile weapon.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/claymore_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',9.0,'Castle Morne: From the main courtyard entrance, hug the right wall and go past the burning corpses with Misbegotten surrounding them. You may aggro one or two along the way. This path leads to the entrance to the building in the north. The sword can be found in a chest to the left just as you enter this building.'),(47,'Iron Greatsword','Greatsword with a blade of unusually thick steel.\r\nA coarse weapon to which polishing is a foreign concept.\r\n\r\nWeighty even among others of its class, the impact of each strike is sure to be felt.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/iron_greatsword_greatswords_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',12.0,'Possible drop from the two Misbegotten Warriors in Leyndell, Royal Capital, in the ash-covered path leading toward the Forbidden Lands. Closest site of grace is the Avenue Balcony in Leyndell. They disappear after progressing past Crumbling Farum Azula. The one near the perfumers can be lured away from the other enemies with ranged attacks.\r\nThe Misbegotten Warrior in Miquella\'s Haligtree, north of the Haligtree Town Plaza Site of Grace. This is the most ideal farming spot as there is a nearby grace and the enemy can be lured toward you with a ranged attack.'),(48,'Lordsworn\'s Greatsword','Well-crafted straight sword with an illustrious design, wielded by regulars of a lord\'s army.\r\n\r\nThrough blackened and damaged by years of use, it appears to have otherwise been kept in a serviceable condition, despite the soldiers having long since lost their minds','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/lordsworns_greatsword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',9.0,'The Lordsworn\'s Greatsword can be looted from a chest in the back of a Carriage, located along the western road leading out of Gatefront Ruins.'),(49,'Knight\'s Greatsword','Greatsword bestowed upon skilled swordsmen in the demigods\' service, and yet had no rank or title.\r\n\r\nFeaturing a long grip enabling a dual-handed use, this weapon was designed to dispatch larger foes. Being charged with such a duty was undoubtedly a great honor.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/knights_greatsword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',10.0,'Dropped by most enemies in the knight archetype such as:\r\nGodrick Knights (throughout Limgrave)\r\nCuckoo Knights (throughout Liurnia of the Lakes)\r\nMausoleum Knight\r\nLeyndell Knights (throughout the Altus Plateau, especially in Leyndell, Royal Capital)\r\nAn easy-to-farm Mausoleum Knight that drops this weapon can be found just outside the Black Knife Catacombs in Liurnia of the Lakes.'),(50,'Banished Knight\'s Greatsword','A finely-crafted greatsword intricately engraved with an ancient motif. Given to knights who, whether by misfortune or misdeed, were forced to abandon their homes. Most of these knights were sent to the fringes, where they were forced to start anew with only despair for company.','https://eldenring.wiki.fextralife.com/file/Elden-Ring/banished_knights_greatsword_weapon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png','SPD_GR',10.0,'Chance for it to be looted off the Banished Knight enemies that you\'ve killed. Can be farmed from the Banished Knight enemies near the Cathedral of Dragon Communion site of grace in Caelid.');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `armi` ENABLE KEYS */;
